new edition spares the frustration ! boyd 's revised edition of virgil 's aeneid is the essential book to prepare for the ap latin : virgil exam or just become familiar with this favorite of all classicists . with all the lines on the ap syllabus and no more , boyd 's aeneid effectively prepares students to be familiar with all the lines that may appear on the test . each page has a paragraph of latin text , with numerous footnotes underneath , offering translation help through grammar and vocabulary hints . a glossary in back serves as quick reference to unfamiliar words . while clyde pharr 's edition has similar detail in footnotes and vocabulary , the pharr text contains all of books 1-9 only , meaning that students have to take home a heavier textbook and also purchase a separate text for books 10-12 of the aeneid . thus , boyd spares students from searching for the passages that will actually be covered : it contains only what is on the syllabus . it is a great way to study virgil 's classic epic